# Trust & Action Engine (Phase 30)

Read **[TRUST_ACTION_ENGINE.md](../../TRUST_ACTION_ENGINE.md)** before changes to action requests, policies, approvals, or emergency stop.

## Rules

1. **Never execute sensitive actions without explicit approval** — Level 4 (critical) is prohibited for AI
2. Every action must be **explainable** (`action_explanations`) and **audited** (`action_audit_logs` + `record_trust_audit_event`)
3. Customer Approval Center is `/app/approvals` — approve/reject via `/api/actions/*`
4. Business logic in Core RPCs — panels are thin clients
5. Emergency stop (`set_tenant_emergency_state`) pauses all pending requests
6. Policies in `action_policies` — skills declare allowed/forbidden actions
7. Platform governance at `/platform/trust` — never expose platform-only controls to Customer App
8. i18n: `locales/{en,no,sv,da}/customerApp.json` (`approvals.*`) and `platform.json` (`trustActions.*`)

## Action levels (risk_level 0–4)

0 information · 1 draft · 2 reversible · 3 sensitive · 4 critical (AI prohibited)
